---
import {getCollection} from "astro:content"; import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro"; import ArchiveNotice from "../../components/ArchiveNotice.astro";
const all=(await getCollection("writing",({data})=>!data.draft&&data.slug!=="legacy-archive")).sort((a,b)=>(b.data.date?.valueOf()||0)-(a.data.date?.valueOf()||0));
---
<BaseLayout title="Writing archive" description="Complete chronological archive of curated and migrated Markdown writing." type="Writing"><header class="page-head"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Archive</p><h1>Every published article, kept in context.</h1><p class="lead">All original Markdown posts are now readable in the new site. Archive notices identify material that has not yet received a fresh technical review.</p></div></header><div class="container content-shell"><aside><ArchiveNotice/></aside><article class="prose"><h2>{all.length} articles</h2><ol>{all.map(item=><li><a href={`/writing/${item.data.slug}/`}>{item.data.title}</a> <span class="small">— {item.data.date?.toISOString().slice(0,10)||"undated"} · {item.data.type}</span></li>)}</ol><h2>Preserved source</h2><p>The exact former Jekyll implementation remains available on <code>legacy-jekyll</code>; each migrated page also retains its original source path and former public URL.</p><p><a href="https://github.com/skcKenneth/skcKenneth.github.io/tree/legacy-jekyll/_posts">Browse original Markdown source on GitHub</a>.</p></article></div></BaseLayout>
